## Association through simultaneity

Once choreography strings and simultaneity families were distinguished, association became more precise.

Association does not mean that one event belongs to many strings.
Instead, association happens when:
- replay of one choreography string reaches an event
- that event sits in a simultaneity family
- the simultaneity family contains events from other strings
- those strings are activated too

This gives the temporal unit more than memory. It gives it:
- association
- resonance
- transfer
- case linkage
- pattern spreading

This led to a strong formulation:

> Cross-choreography coupling does not occur because one event belongs to many strings, but because distinct events are clocked within the same temporal slice.

That is now a key design principle.

