## Φ as simultaneity / non-simultaneity coupling

A further important idea emerged around Φ.

If choreography strings are distinct longitudinal families, and coherence arises from their temporal coupling through simultaneity, then Φ may be understood as a measure of how strongly distinct longitudinal strings are coupled through simultaneity families relative to how independently they are unfolding.

This gives a new interpretation of Φ inside the temporal unit:
- not as collapse of all strings into one
- but as the degree of synchronically meaningful coupling among differentiated lines

This also gave weight a new meaning.

Weight is not only:
- persistence within one string
- repetition frequency
- rate of change
- resistance to decay

Weight may also arise from:
- how many choreography strings are co-firing in the same slice
- how strong the simultaneity coupling is
- how broad the coherence field becomes

This made simultaneity itself a contributor to weight.

The result was a strong refinement:

> Coherence is not the collapse of many choreography strings into one, but the sustained simultaneity relation among distinct strings that remain longitudinally differentiated while temporally coupled.

This was recognized as a powerful temporal interpretation of coherence conservation.

