## Temporal unit as case-unravelling engine

By combining event clocking, replay, association, simultaneity, and coherence cutoff, the temporal unit was recognized as something more than a state manager.

It became:

- a corridor initiator
- an event clocker
- a replay engine
- an associative spread engine
- a divergence detector
- and ultimately a **case-unravelling engine**

This means that a pile of events is not yet an intelligible history.
The temporal unit turns it into:
- sequence
- weighted sequence
- interacting sequence
- case-specific morphology

This was captured in the formulation:

> The temporal unit is not only a forward-weighting device. It is also a case-unravelling engine: it reconstructs the becoming of the present by re-walking the event corridor and re-weighting each step in light of the whole.

This is one of the strongest engineering interpretations to emerge from the dialogue.

