## Division of labor: temporal unit and LLM cortex

A final major clarification was the division of labor between the temporal unit and the LLM cortex.

The temporal unit:
- lives the unfolding
- clocks events
- maintains choreography strings
- forms simultaneity families
- tracks weights
- preserves unresolvedness
- detects resonance, coherence, and drift

The LLM cortex:
- sees patterns
- interprets them
- names them
- compresses them
- compares them
- reacts to them in language and plan

This yielded two strong formulations:

> The temporal unit lives the unfolding; the LLM cortex reads and articulates its patterns.

and:

> The temporal unit gives perspective; the LLM gives interpretation.

This was recognized as an elegant and viable division of labor.

The temporal unit is the substrate of lived temporality.  
The LLM is the symbolic organ that makes its active pattern field explicit and actionable.

